ician  [Long Post]</span><hr size=1>  I just wanted to share some of my knowledge and experience  of the mage class with anyone interested in starting a Mage.<br>
Yes, it can be done, as you may have seen others mention.<br>
Here is my method for soloing:<br>
 If you are a caster, you should be fairly good at judging the maximum range from which your spells will hit your target. The fire bolt line of spells is a great puller from long distances. Park your pet on a safe spot, usually near a wall [i.e. Rathe Mountains] or the shore of an island [i.e. Ocean of Tears], etc. <br>
[Note: it helps to have SoW, SoW potions or Journeymans boots.]<br>
 Now, go find your intended victim and hit it with a bolt. Turn and run to your pet. Here it helps to have hot key #1 say &quot;/Pet attack&quot; and #2 &quot;/pet back off.&quot; That way you have control of your best friend, and main source of defense, at all times. Hot keys #3 - #10 can be your damage shield (used mainly on pet and tanks) as well as your offensive spells and, if you are like me, &quot;GATE&quot; is ALWAYS UP while soloing!<br>
 I recommend using your best bolt (for pulling), best DD/fire (during battle), best DD/Blade or DD/Sword type spell (for those fire resistant mobs!), one debuff or Malosi type spell (here you can substitute pet buff or heal spell) and one lower level FAST DD/spell for those last few hps, when you don't need to use 250+ mana.<br>
Where was I? Oh yeah.<br>
 So, now that you have run back to your pet at top speed, with a huge head start, thanks to the long range of your bolt, sit behind it and hit hotkey #1 just as the mob approaches it. I normally use Earth pet for it's high HPs and it's abilty to root. (If you have the means, give it 2 velium swords for a bit of extra damage. Spend some time in SoV and loot a few bags full.)<br>
 Watch the health bar of your target - f8, and your pet - toggle f1, and keep doing damage to the target as necessary to keep your pet's health bar higher than the target, or YOU may become the next target! (* See &quot;Kiting&quot; below.)<br>
 If you are close enough to your pet, you can type &quot;/pet report health.&quot; Better yet, make a bunch of hot keys for pet commands on one of your &quot;social&quot; banks, and feel free to add emotes or other entertaining commands here. [See me in game for further instruction on this.] My #1 hotkey says &quot;Cien points at %T and orders his pet to kill! My #2 hotkey says &quot;Cien orders his pet to take a valium!<br>
[Note: &quot;%T&quot; indicates your target. Your pet will only attack an NPC or an arena opponent, not you nor another PC outside of the arena.]<br>
 Sit/med between casting, and try to keep as much mana in reserve as you can. Let your pet do as much damage as it can, while you throw in the occasional DD. Don't let your mana bar drop faster than your pet's HP bar, because it can heal faster than you med in most cases. (Clarity and Breeze will offset that.)<br>
 I don't believe in the rumors that letting your pet &quot;make the kill&quot; results in less xp, but if you think it's a problem, just call your pet off at the last second and use a fast, low level DD spell to finish your target off.<br>
<br>
Now my method for &quot;Kiting&quot;:<br>
 If you want to solo something that you know is too tough for you, follow the above instructions for pulling, however...<br>
 Instead of sitting behind your pet, run to a safe distance and sit. (about the range of a bolt is good.) Instead of the pet buff/heal spell, keep a pet summon spell memmed. Target your pet and wait for it to die. Immediately stand and summon a pet! It takes practice to work out a safe distance, so keep some sow potions available untill you get your Jboots. As the mob approaches you, target it and send your pet. (hotkey #1)<br>
Repeat as necessary.<br>
<br>
Today I soloed the Allizewsaur 2 times, and used 15 pets, so I know it can be done. (This works best if the target is NOT a caster.) Malachite only costs a few gp each, so I keep several stacks on me at all times. By the way, I must have circled that island 30+ times while killing that thing. Didn't get much xp, but I did gain some experience on staying alive. Sheeesh, it would have been much easier with Clarity II.<br>
<br>
I hope this helps some of you lower level mages. Maybe it will encourage some of you to start a mage. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I'm always willing to learn new tricks too, if anyone would like to share your secrets.<br>
<br>
Also, see me if you need spells researched. I have high skill and spare components. Bring me the spell and I'll make it.<br>
